This paper is primarily focused on Neural Architecture Search (NAS), which is a subfield of machine learning and artificial intelligence. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of large-scale datasets, which suggests that it may also be relevant to computer vision (cs.CV) and data science (cs.DS). The paper also proposes a systematic approach to measure the importance of each example, which could be relevant to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and neural networks (cs.NE).
